subject: p19159236
Findings: Persistent pulmonary opacities, vascular engorgement and septal lines refkect mild pulmonary edema. Small left pleural effusion cannot be excluded. Low lung volumes limit assessment of cardiomediastinal silhouette though the cardiac size appears mildly enlarged.
Impression: Unchanged mild pulmonary edema with likely small left pleural effusion.
